LICENSE PLACEHOLDER

Choose a license for your project before publishing or sharing it.

Common options:

- **MIT** — permissive, simple. Anyone can do almost anything with it. Use if you want maximum adoption and don't care about commercial use.

- **Apache 2.0** — permissive with patent grant. Better protection than MIT for projects with patentable ideas. Use for most commercial-friendly open source.

- **GPL v3** — copyleft. Derivative works must also be GPL. Use if you want to ensure modifications stay open.

- **AGPL v3** — strong copyleft including network use. Required modification disclosure even for SaaS. Use if you want to prevent SaaS-without-contribution.

- **BSL (Business Source License)** — temporarily proprietary, transitions to open. Use for commercial products you may open-source later.

- **Proprietary / All Rights Reserved** — closed source. Use for commercial products you don't want others to use.

For private projects with no public component, you can leave this file empty or delete it.

For Canadian context: licenses are governed by contract law. None of the above are jurisdiction-specific, but they should be reviewed by a lawyer for any commercial deployment.

Once chosen, replace the entire contents of this file with the license text.
Common templates: https://choosealicense.com
